        "last_activity_date": 1629297677,
        "creation_date": 1629295665,
        "body": "<p>Any JDBC 4.3 driver will also be compliant with JDBC 4.2 (as the JDBC 4.3 specification includes everything from JDBC 4.2). So, if a library requires at least JDBC 4.2, then it will also work with a JDBC 4.3 driver.<\/p>\n<p>This does assume - of course - that the library itself is able to run on Java 9 (which introduced JDBC 4.3) or higher, but given Hibernate is tested on - at least - Java 8 and Java 11, that would be the case.<\/p>\n<p>As far as I'm aware, Hibernate does not use any features introduced in JDBC 4.3.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 68833988,
        "question_id": 68822625,
        "last_edit_date": 1629297677
    }],
